examples.en: 'My name's not Sonny,' the child objected.
They objected that the price was too high.
I objected to having to rewrite the article.
No one objected when the paintings were removed.
She objected that the accusation was based on hearsay.
Robson strongly objected to the terms of the contract.
When asked to drive the truck, she objected that she did not have a driver's license.
I objected to the manner in which the decision was made.
Many communists objected to any form of private property.
He objected strenuously to the stand his party was taking.
He objected to the allowance of smoking in the dining room.
We can't buy the chair, he objected. It won't fit in the car.
She never objected to the amount of work her boss charged her with.
The group objected that the policy would prevent patients from receiving the best treatment.
One writer objected to what she described as the bile that is spewed from the newspaper's editorial page.
